<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Turtle Shelter Vests</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        /* General Dark Mode Styling */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #181818; /* Darker background */
            color: #cccccc; /* Softer light text */
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        /* Banner Section with Gradient Fade */
        .banner {
            background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9)), 
                        url('/redblueorangevests.png') no-repeat center top;
            background-size: cover;
            background-attachment: fixed;
            height: 600px;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            text-align: center;
            color: white;
            font-size: 2rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            width: 100%;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        /* Image and Text Section */
        .image-text-container {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 15px;
            margin: 15px auto;
            max-width: 90%; /* Compact width */
        }

        .image-text-container img {
            width: 45%; /* Slightly smaller images */
            border-radius: 8px;
            transition: box-shadow 0.3s ease;
        }

        .image-text-container img:hover {
            box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
        }

        .image-text-container p {
            flex: 1;
            text-align: left;
            margin: 0;
        }

        p {
            text-align: center;
            margin: 10px auto;
            max-width: 85%;
        }

        /* Carousel Section */
        .carousel img {
            max-height: 600px; /* Compact carousel */
            object-fit: cover;
            max-width: 500px;
        }

        .carousel-control-prev-icon,
        .carousel-control-next-icon {
            background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
            border-radius: 50%;
        }

        /* Links and Buttons */
        a {
            color: #7a9aff;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        a:hover {
            color: #4a6cd1;
        }

        button {
            background-color: #4a6cd1;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 8px 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        button:hover {
            background-color: #7a9aff;
        }

        /* Footer Styling */
        footer {
            background-color: #222222;
            padding: 15px;
            text-align: center;
            color: #888888;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        footer a {
            color: #7a9aff;
        }

        footer a:hover {
            color: #4a6cd1;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Navigation Bar -->
    <%- include('partials/navbar', { page: 'home' }) %>

    <!-- Banner Section -->
    <div class="banner">
        Saving Lives with Turtle Shelter Vests
    </div>

    <!-- Explain Turtle Project -->
    <p>What is a turtle shelter vest? A high-tech but simple solution to help save lives - a portable "shelter" you can carry with you, just like a turtle...</p>

    <!-- Image and Text Section -->
    <div class="image-text-container">
        <p>One winter when Jen was homeless, 7 of her friends froze to death.  

        Jen is no longer homeless and has figured out a solution:
        High-tech foam vests that are inexpensive,
        keep a person warm to 10 degrees below zero, help SAVE lives, and alleviate suffering.
        
        YOU can request vests for your community - and you can make vests and have your friends, business colleagues, church members, or club make vests, too!</p>
    </div>

    <iframe src="https://www.facebook.com/plugins/video.php?height=314&href=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Famericafirstcu%2Fvideos%2F1530868333944560%2F&show_text=false&width=560&t=0" width="560" height="314" style="border:none;overflow:hidden" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="true" allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowFullScreen="true"></iframe>

    <!-- Vests Distributed Section -->
    <p>Over 5,500 vests have been made and distributed by volunteers like you.</p>

    <!-- Carousel Section -->
    <div id="vestCarousel" class="carousel slide" data-bs-ride="carousel">
        <div class="carousel-inner">
            <div class="carousel-item active">
                <img src="/vest1.jpg" class="d-block w-100" alt="Vest 1">
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <img src="/vest2.jpg" class="d-block w-100" alt="Vest 2">
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <img src="/vest3.jpg" class="d-block w-100" alt="Vest 3">
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <img src="/vest4.jpg" class="d-block w-100" alt="Vest 4">
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <img src="/vest5.jpg" class="d-block w-100" alt="Vest 5">
            </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Controls -->
        <button class="carousel-control-prev" type="button" data-bs-target="#vestCarousel" data-bs-slide="prev">
            <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="visually-hidden">Previous</span>
        </button>
        <button class="carousel-control-next" type="button" data-bs-target="#vestCarousel" data-bs-slide="next">
            <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="visually-hidden">Next</span>
        </button>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer>
        &copy; 2024 Turtle Shelter Vests | <a href="#">Privacy Policy</a> | <a href="#">Terms of Service</a>
    </footer>

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
